narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Personal skills, language skills, learning skills, Indonesian language and culture.
Public speaking, southeast Asian studies knowledge

By the end of this course, I was able to understand almost everything Bu Dinny said and was able to participate in conversations without feeling as though I was unequipped. Beyond learning the language to a high level. I developed an in-depth understanding of Indonesian culture. This includes topics such as religion, differences in perception, habits and hobbies, work and much more.
the language as a whole and even parts of the indonesian culture
Deep dive into Indonesian culture and language. Very interesting learning about local culture and current socio-political problems in Indonesia
More knowledge and insight regarding the Indonesian culture in a great depth. Both into traditional and current Indonesian life
Developed my understanding of the Indonesian language. Also learned a lot about Indonesian culture.
I leaned about the Indonesian language, culture, and way of life. I made such close bonds with my fellow classmates and had fun in class.

I gained extensive knowledge on the Indonesian culture and am now able to hold my own in conversation. I learned about Indonesian architecture, different cities in Indonesia, as well as unique cultural experiences such as songs and dances.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Taught fantastically
I loved the professor. Bu Dinny is so sweet and makes class a great time.
The general class format was a major strength, with a large amount of general discussion and listening, all in bahasa Indonesia
Bu Dinny is Yales greatest asset. Great Professor and great person. The most enjoyable and satisfying class Ive taken at Yale.
Strengths are that Bu is a great teacher, highly engaging, and the format of sitting having a conversation type of set up is much better than a lecture style
One of the few classes I look forward to attending everyday. Few weaknesses but sometimes assignment deadlines arent too clear.

The professor of this course is unbelievable. She is the best teacher I have ever had and she truly cares about all of her students. She made a great curriculum that is great for learning at a good pace and especially understanding the language. There honestly were no weaknesses.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: YES. Bu Dinny is the best professor and the best human who gets to know her students on a very personal level.
Absolutely. The professor is amazing and the class is a great group of people.

Absolutely. For anyone vaguely interested in Indonesia and the language, this class was highly insightful and allowed for a high level of fluency in the language. Bu Dinny is great and makes class very engaging and fun.
yes, a great way to earn language credit while enjoying the class

If I could take Indonesian L1 through L4 again Id do it every day if the week. The most enjoyable class Ive taken at Yale. Id recommend it to everyone whos interested in learning about a new culture you otherwise would never have an understanding of.
Yes absolutely. If you want to learn more about the culture and language in Indonesia this is a very engaging course
Definitely, it was a great class and Bu Dinny always brought a smile to class.
Yes 100%. I met some great people in this course and got to learn a new language. There isnt much more you could ask for out of a language course.
